FBIS3-57748 "drsov020bb_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 January 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS International Economic Forum Held in Davos Outlines Plans for Investment Council LD3001192394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1800 GMT 30 Jan 94 LD3001192394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin presented a proposal for a multilateral council of foreign and Russian bankers, investors, and entrepreneurs. He announced this at the world economic forum in Davos. Chernomyrdin believes this council could be convened this May-July in Moscow. Chernomyrdin thinks that Russia can use about $10-12 billion in foreign investments. He emphasized that conditions for foreign investors in Russia is gradually improving.
